@startuml
title Projet 12 — Architecture applicative (FastAPI + Streamlit + ML + SQLite)

left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "Utilisateur" as User

node "Machine locale / serveur" as Host {

  node "Docker Compose / exécution locale" as Runtime {

    package "Frontend" {
      component "Streamlit UI\nui/streamlit_app.py" as Streamlit
      component "UI économique\nui/economics_ui.py" as EconUI
    }

    package "Backend API" {
      component "FastAPI\napp/main.py" as FastAPI
      component "Schemas\napp/schemas.py" as Schemas
      component "Services métier\napp/services.py" as Services
      component "Model Loader\napp/model_loader.py" as Loader
      component "Economics Store\napp/economics_store.py" as EconStore
    }

    database "SQLite\n data/reference/economics.sqlite" as SQLiteDB

    folder "Artifacts\nmodèles + métadonnées" as Artifacts

    component "Script d'initialisation\nscripts/init_economics_db.py" as InitDB
  }
}

cloud "GitHub" as GitHub {
  component "GitHub Actions CI\nlint + format + tests + builds Docker" as CI
}

User --> Streamlit : utilise l'interface
User --> FastAPI : consulte /docs ou appelle l'API

Streamlit --> FastAPI : /predict, /recommend,\nlecture/édition économique
EconUI --> FastAPI : actions économiques

FastAPI --> Schemas : validation I/O
FastAPI --> Services : orchestration métier

Services --> Loader : chargement / accès modèles
Loader --> Artifacts : .joblib + métadonnées

Services --> EconStore : lecture/écriture économique
EconStore --> SQLiteDB : SQL

InitDB --> SQLiteDB : initialise les tables\ncrop_prices / crop_costs

CI --> GitHub : déclenchée sur push / PR
CI --> Runtime : build Docker API + UI
CI --> FastAPI : tests API
CI --> Streamlit : vérification build UI

note right of Services
Logique métier principale :
- prédiction de rendement
- recommandation de cultures
- calcul revenu / coûts / marge brute
- choix du modèle approprié
end note

note bottom of SQLiteDB
Données économiques V1 :
- prix par culture
- coûts variables par hectare
end note

@enduml